<LocalizedProperties><Language>en</Language><Title>Microsoft .NET Framework 3.5, Windows Vista SP1, and Windows Server 2008 Security Update for x64-based Systems (KB979913)</Title><Description>A security issue has been identified that could allow an attacker to tamper with digitally signed content without being detected, when this content is being consumed by an application that makes use of the Microsoft .NET Framework on a Windows-based system. You can help protect your computer by installing this update from Microsoft. After you install this item, you may have to restart your computer.</Description><UninstallNotes>This software update can be removed by selecting View installed updates in the Programs and Features Control Panel.</UninstallNotes><MoreInfoUrl>http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=185340</MoreInfoUrl><SupportUrl>http://support.microsoft.com/</SupportUrl></LocalizedProperties>